               <P>The council will observe a minimum 10 calendar days standstill period following the publication of this notice before entering into the contract. If an appeal regarding the award of contract has not been successfully resolved. The Public Contracts Regulations 2015 (SI 2015 nº 102) provide for aggrieved parties to take legal action. Any such action must be brought within the applicable limitation period. Where a contract has not been entered into, the Court may order the setting aside of the award decision or order the council to amend any document and may award damages. If the contract has been entered into the Court may, depending on the circumstances, award damages, make a declaration of ineffectiveness, order the relevant authority to pay a fine, and /or order that the duration of the contract be shortened. The purpose of the standstill period referred above is to allow the parties to apply to the Courts to set aside the award decision before a contract is entered into.</P>
